_r_e_t_u_r_n_s _c_e_l_l _d_i_m_e_n_s_i_o_n_s _f_o_r _a _v_o_x_e_l _o_r _p_i_x_e_l _u_n_i_t

_D_e_s_c_r_i_p_t_i_o_n:

     generic function to access the voxel or pixel dimension for a
     brain image

_U_s_a_g_e:

     spacing(x)

_A_r_g_u_m_e_n_t_s:

       x: object derived from "BrainSpace" or "BrainData" classes 

_V_a_l_u_e:

     a numeric vector of the cell sizes for each image axis

_N_o_t_e:

     this function does not deal with non-spatial dimensions, such as
     time.  Thus, a 4-D fMRI image return a vector of length 3, one for
     each spatail dimension.

